## 12. Pushed Authorization Requests (PAR) — RFC 9126

Pushes authorization params server-to-server before the redirect, returning a short-lived `request_uri`. Prevents parameter tampering. PingOne supports PAR — set `parRequirement: REQUIRED` or `OPTIONAL` on the app.

```javascript
// Step 1: POST /as/par  (same params as /authorize, sent server-to-server)
// Auth: Basic base64(clientId:clientSecret)
// Response: { request_uri: 'urn:ietf:params:oauth:request_uri:...', expires_in: 60 }

// Step 2: Redirect with only client_id + request_uri (omit all other params)
res.redirect(`${AUTH_BASE}/authorize?client_id=${CLIENT_ID}&request_uri=${encodeURIComponent(requestUri)}`);
// parTimeout app setting: 1–600 seconds (default 60)
```

