## 13. OIDC ID Token Validation

PingOne id_tokens are RS256-signed JWTs. Full validation:

```javascript
// 1. Decode header to get kid
const { header, payload } = jwt.decode(idToken, { complete: true });

// 2. Fetch JWKS from /as/jwks — select key matching header.kid
//    Use jwks-rsa package for automatic key fetching + caching

// 3. Verify signature (RS256 typically)
const verified = jwt.verify(idToken, publicKey, { algorithms: ['RS256'] });

// 4. Verify issuer
if (payload.iss !== `https://auth.pingone.${region}/${envId}/as`) throw Error('iss invalid');

// 5. Verify audience contains client_id
if (![].concat(payload.aud).includes(clientId)) throw Error('aud invalid');

// 6. Verify not expired
if (payload.exp * 1000 < Date.now()) throw Error('token expired');

// 7. Verify nonce (replay prevention)
if (payload.nonce !== sessionNonce) throw Error('nonce mismatch');

// 8. (Optional) Verify acr  if step-up was requested
// 9. (Optional) Verify at_hash against access token for hybrid flows
```

`SKIP_TOKEN_SIGNATURE_VALIDATION=true` skips steps 2–3 for local dev only. **Never in production.**

