## 14. Scope Configuration

### Standard OIDC Scopes

| Scope | Description | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `openid` | Signals OIDC; enables id_token | Required for all OIDC flows |
| `profile` | name, given_name, family_name | Auth code, CIBA |
| `email` | email, email_verified | Auth code, CIBA |
| `offline_access` | Adds refresh_token to response | Must be in PingOne resource grant; add scope to app |

### Project Custom Scopes

| Scope | Client | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `banking:read` | User client | Read accounts/transactions |
| `banking:write` | User client | Transfer/payment actions |
| `banking:admin` | Admin client | User management, admin config |

### PingOne Management API Scopes (Worker app)

| Scope | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `p1:read:user` | Read user directory |
| `p1:update:user` | Update user attributes |
| `p1:update:userMfaEnabled` | Enable/disable MFA per user |
| `p1:create:userMfaEnabled` | Create MFA enrollment |
| `p1:delete:user` | Delete a user |

**Scope setup in PingOne:** Applications → (App) → Resource Access → add scopes. Multiple custom resource scopes require `requestScopesForMultipleResourcesEnabled: true` on the app.

