## 20. Security Checklist

- ✅ PKCE S256 on every authorization code flow
- ✅ State validated on every callback (CSRF prevention)
- ✅ Nonce validated in id_token (replay attack prevention)
- ✅ Redirect URIs validated server-side before constructing auth URL
- ✅ Tokens in server-side session only — never in localStorage or response body
- ✅ Session cookies: HttpOnly, Secure, SameSite=Lax
- ✅ RFC 7009 revocation on logout (both access + refresh)
- ✅ `SKIP_TOKEN_SIGNATURE_VALIDATION=false` enforced in production
- ✅ Admin session cleared before user/customer login (prevents role confusion)
- ✅ Rate limiting on all `/api/auth/*` endpoints
- ✅ Correlation IDs on all PingOne requests
- ✅ `act`/`may_act` claims validated on token-exchanged tokens
- ✅ Scope enforcement middleware on all resource routes
- ✅ `CLIENT_SECRET_BASIC` (Authorization header) — never send `client_secret` in body alongside `code_verifier`
- ✅ `additionalRefreshTokenReplayProtectionEnabled` enabled on PingOne app
- ❌ Never use implicit flow (`response_type=token` or `response_type=id_token` only)
- ❌ Never log raw tokens — log type, expiry, and event type only
- ❌ Never expose `client_secret` to the browser/frontend
- ❌ Never skip CIBA `slow_down` — always back off
- ❌ Never use `prompt=none` without gracefully handling `interaction_required`

