## 22. OIDC Discovery

Use the discovery doc to avoid hardcoding URLs and to check supported features:

```javascript
// GET https://auth.pingone.{tld}/{envId}/as/.well-known/openid-configuration
// Cache this response — only changes on PingOne environment updates

// Key fields returned:
// authorization_endpoint, token_endpoint, userinfo_endpoint, jwks_uri
// introspection_endpoint, revocation_endpoint
// backchannel_authentication_endpoint         ← CIBA
// device_authorization_endpoint               ← Device grant
// pushed_authorization_request_endpoint       ← PAR
// grant_types_supported, scopes_supported
// code_challenge_methods_supported            ← should include 'S256'
// backchannel_token_delivery_modes_supported  ← 'poll', 'ping'
```

